                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>አብ፡ ወወ፡ ወመ፡</abbr> for <expan>አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ </expan>
                                 (<locus from="14r" to="15r">14r-15r</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the Patriarch of Alexandria
                           and of the Metropolitan; incipit of Texts I-II; directives to the
                           minister and their abbreviations; name or initial lines of the prayers to
                           be read; part of the abbreviation of the Trinitarian formula (fols.
                           14r-15r); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 On the incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i1">Text I</ref>
                           (fol. <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>), few lines are rubricated
                           (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
